Eucalyptus tenuis is a tree that is native to Western Australia.The tree typically grows to a height of 3 to 12 metres (10 to 39 ft) and has smooth bark and a thin whipstick habit. It blooms around March producing inflorescences with cream coloured flowers.
It is found on undulating plains in an area between Kalgoorlie in the north to the Norseman in the south where it grows in red sandy-loam-clay soils.
